The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 10 November is 302,006 (34,808 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 05 November, there were 452 new confirmed cases (52.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 29 October, there were 550 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 18% (98 fewer cases).
